  <data name="Aug_Rotate90CW_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Creates a deterministic copy by rotating the tile 90° clockwise.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Rotate90CW_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Useful when objects can appear in any orientation relative to the map axis.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Rotate180_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Creates a deterministic copy flipped 180°.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Rotate180_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Improves model robustness to inverted scene orientation.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Rotate270CW_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Creates a deterministic copy by rotating the tile 270° clockwise.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Rotate270CW_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Add together with other rotations for full orientation coverage.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_FlipH_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Creates a horizontally mirrored copy.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_FlipH_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Improves robustness to left/right object variations.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_FlipV_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Creates a vertically mirrored copy.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_FlipV_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Use with caution: often useful for aerial data, but may introduce unrealistic scenes.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_ShearX_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Shears the image along the X axis, simulating a perspective shift.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_ShearX_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Moderate values (up to 5–10°) are usually sufficient; larger values may distort objects.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_ShearY_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Shears the image along the Y axis.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_ShearY_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Use together with Shear X for robustness to oblique viewpoints.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Scale_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Scales the scene, changing the relative size of objects.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Scale_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>A range of about 0.8–1.2 usually gives a realistic effect without significant degradation.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_TranslateX_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Shifts the image horizontally.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_TranslateX_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Useful for training on offset objects; too large a shift increases the proportion of clipped annotations.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_TranslateY_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Shifts the image vertically.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_TranslateY_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Keep the value moderate to avoid losing annotations at the frame edge.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Perspective_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Adds perspective distortion to simulate a change in viewpoint.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Perspective_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Start with small values (0.0005–0.001) to avoid strong deformation.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_RandomCrop_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Randomly crops the image, keeping the selected fraction of the original frame.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_RandomCrop_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Lowering the parameter increases diversity but may increase the number of empty tiles.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Hue_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Shifts the hue in HSV, changing the color tone of objects and background.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Hue_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Useful under varying lighting conditions and seasons.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Saturation_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Changes color saturation.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Saturation_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Avoid extremes to prevent unnatural textures.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Brightness_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Adjusts image brightness.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Brightness_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Small fluctuations help the model generalize between bright and dark scenes.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Contrast_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Increases or decreases contrast between object and background.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Contrast_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Moderate contrast is useful for robustness to different sensors/exposures.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_CLAHE_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Locally equalizes contrast, enhancing details in dark and bright areas.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_CLAHE_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Use moderately to avoid amplifying noise.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_AutoContrast_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Automatically stretches the histogram by clipping extreme values.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_AutoContrast_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Works well for heterogeneous images with unstable exposure.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Grayscale_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Converts the image to grayscale with a given probability.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Grayscale_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Helps reduce the model's dependence on color when shape/texture matters more.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Solarize_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Inverts pixels above a threshold, creating a high-contrast effect.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Solarize_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Use rarely and with low probability as regularization.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Posterize_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Reduces the number of bits per channel, simplifying color gradations.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Posterize_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Suitable for improving robustness to quantization/compression.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Equalize_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Globally equalizes the brightness histogram.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Equalize_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Useful for equalizing contrast across different scenes.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_GaussianBlur_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Blurs the image with a Gaussian filter.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_GaussianBlur_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Simulates defocus/motion blur; apply large kernels carefully.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_MedianBlur_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Median blur suppresses impulse noise while preserving edges.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_MedianBlur_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Works well on noisy images without significant loss of contours.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_GaussianNoise_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Adds Gaussian noise to pixels.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_GaussianNoise_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Improves robustness to noisy sensors, but excess degrades label quality.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_SaltPepper_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Adds impulse noise (white/black dots).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_SaltPepper_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Use low density to simulate transmission/compression artifacts.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_RandomShadow_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Overlays artificial shadows.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_RandomShadow_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Useful for aerial photos with variable lighting; don't overuse the application rate.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_RainFog_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Simulates atmospheric rain/fog effects.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_RainFog_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Moderate intensity improves model transferability to bad weather.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Mosaic_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Combines 4 images into one to increase object density.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Mosaic_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Strong augmentation for train; enable carefully for stable validation.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_MixUp_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Linearly blends two images and their annotations.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_MixUp_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Low alpha values usually give the best balance between regularization and readability.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_CopyPaste_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Copies objects between images to increase class variability.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_CopyPaste_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Useful for class imbalance and rare objects.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_CutOut_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Randomly hides image fragments with rectangular cutouts.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_CutOut_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Helps with occlusion robustness, but large areas may remove important features.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Erasing_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Probabilistically erases random image regions.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Erasing_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Use low/medium probability for moderate regularization.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Default_Desc" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Transform modifies the appearance of training images.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Aug_Default_Rec" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Adjust parameters gradually and check the effect in Preview.</value>
  </data>
